        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Syracuse</placeName>, <date>Monday, 6<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi>
                    <add>?</add></date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>(July) 1854</date>.</p>
            <p>May the Lord comfort his pious ones in<lb/> accordance with the multitude of his<lb/>
                favors; and all those who mourn for the<lb/> captivity of
                    <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>. May they see the<lb/> rebuilding of the house
                of the living God,<lb/> and among them my friend the wise etc. <persName>Isaac<lb/>
                    Leeser</persName>.</p>
            <p>Dear Friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">This week I <del>received a letter</del> learned from a<lb/> friend
                in <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> that my letter about<lb/>
                <persName>Lilienthal</persName> and which appeared in the “Occi-<lb/>dent” was
                copied in other German news-<lb/>papers. I believe also in the “Judenzeitung.”<lb/>
                I am very curious to see and to know <del>under</del><lb/> with what intention it
                was copied. You<lb/> will therefore oblige me greatly if you<lb/> had the kindness
                to send me this news-<lb/>paper. Please do me this favor. I am<lb/> always ready to
                do you a service in<lb/> return.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Respectfully,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Issachar Baer</persName>, son of
                    <persName>Rabbi<lb/>J</persName>—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Dr. B. Illowy</persName>.</p>
        </body>
